## Setup

**In `.cursor/.envrc`:**
```bash
export CONFLUENCE_URL="https://company.atlassian.net/wiki"
export CONFLUENCE_EMAIL="email@company.com"
export CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN="your-token"
```

**Note:** If Confluence credentials are not set, JIRA credentials will be used automatically (same Atlassian account). The setup script auto-configures Confluence when you set up JIRA.

**Fallback order:**
1. `CONFLUENCE_URL` → falls back to `${JIRA_URL}/wiki`
2. `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL` → falls back to `JIRA_EMAIL`
3. `CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN` → falls back to `JIRA_API_TOKEN`

**Get API Token:**
1. Go to https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
2. Create new token (same token works for both JIRA and Confluence)
3. Add to .cursor/.envrc

